Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis, Piedmont type

definition.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis (HCHWA), Piedmont type is a form of HCHWA (see this term) characterized by an age of onset between 50-70 years of age, recurrent lobar intracerebral hemorrhages and cognitive decline.

label.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis, Iowa type

definition.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis (HCHWA), Iowa type is a form of HCHWA (see this term) characterized by age of onset between 50-66 years of age, memory impairment, myoclonic jerks, expressive dysphagia, short-stepped gait, personality changes and lobar intracerebral hemorrhages.

label.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis, Italian type

definition.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis (HCHWA), Italian type is a form of HCHWA (see this term) characterized by an age of onset of 50 years of age, dementia and lobar intracerebral hemorrhage.

label.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis, Flemish type

definition.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis (HCHWA), Flemish type is a form of HCHWA (see this term) characterized by an age of onset of 45 years of age, progressive Alzheimer's disease-like dementia and lobar intracerebral hemorrhage in some patients.

label.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis, Arctic type

definition.value: Hereditary cerebral hemorrhage with amyloidosis (HCHWA), Arctic type is a form of HCHWA (see this term) characterized by an age of onset of 54-61 years and progressive Alzheimer's disease-like dementia, without intracerebral hemorrhages.

Joint contractures, muscle atrophy, microcytic anemia and panniculitis-induced lipodystrophy (JMP) syndrome is a rare autoinflammatory disorder belonging to the proteasome disability syndrome (see this term) group and characterized by sclerodermic skin with the presence of erythematous lesions, joint contractures, generalized or partial lipodystrophy, muscle atrophy and short stature.

Chronic atypical neutrophilic dermatosis with lipodystrophy and elevated temperature (CANDLE) syndrome is a rare autoinflammatory disorder belonging to the proteasome disability syndrome (see this term) group and is characterized by early-onset recurrent fever, swollen violaceous eyelids, progressive lipodystrophy, arthralgia, purpuric skin lesions and delayed physical development.
